FAQ

  • Does Square have tools for complex businesses?

    Square has solutions for businesses of all sizes. Our connected tools are built to scale with future-focused, connected tools. Enhanced, customer-friendly experiences help build deeper data and better customer relationships. And our open platform means you can connect to prebuilt integrations or build out your own with our APIs. Learn how Square works with larger, more complex businesses .

  • What are merchant services?

    Merchant services is an all-encompassing term that describes the hardware, software, and financial services needed for a business to accept and process payments — credit cards, debit cards, NFC-enabled mobile wallets, and other contactless payments — both online and in-store.

    Just getting started and need a simple way to take payments? Your first Square Reader for magstripe is free when you sign up for an account. Additional readers are $10.

  • Does Square have tools for professional services businesses?

    Square built a suite of integrated tools to help service businesses save time so they can focus on growing revenue and delivering exceptional service to their clients. Square Appointments works for any business that needs appointment scheduling capabilities and a point-of-sale system. Use Square Invoices — a free, all-in-one invoicing solution that helps businesses request, track, and manage their invoices, estimates, and payments in one place — to get paid faster. And Square Messages is a platform designed to keep your client communication (texts, emails, receipts, invoices, feedback, checkout links, and more) in one place; you can send and receive texts online, and your clients experience more immediate customer service. Learn more about our solutions for professional services .

  • How does buy now, pay later work?

    Buy now, pay later , or BNPL, is a payment option that allows a customer to pay for a purchase over time in installments while merchants get paid in full. With Afterpay, Square merchants can let customers pay in four interest-free installments over six weeks.

  • How does Square compare to other business software providers?

    Square’s point of sale software and suite of tools makes it easy to sell in person, online, over the phone, or out in the field. As your business evolves, you can quickly add tools that help your business, from managing team members to adding devices and locations, all with a couple of taps. You can also track customers’ preferences and purchases to create more personalized marketing and loyalty programs to keep them coming back more often. We stand out with best-in-class hardware and an all-in-one platform.

    See how we stack up against Shopify, Toast, Gusto, Vagaro, and others with a
    feature-by-feature comparison . Or hear what our customers have to say about Square on our review page .

  • What kind of resources does Square provide businesses?

    Square not only strives to provide the best hardware and software, but also the resources to support you in every stage of your journey, whether you’re a first-time business owner, or a seasoned entrepreneur. Brush up on your basics with our business glossary . Explore our publications for modern business leaders, Town Square , for the latest trends, insights, and strategies. Or find tips and tricks, videos, and articles in our Support Center to help you get the most out of Square hardware and software. Need a little extra help? Our team is ready to help you via phone, email, Facebook, or Twitter.

My name is Dominick Lewis. I’m the owner of Photodom, an analogue camera store based in Brooklyn, New York.

My role at Photodom is a little bit of everything. I’m either working in the lab, or sometimes in the store

sometimes repairing cameras, working with the marketing team, or handling customer service — so, it’s a little bit of everything.

My official role in the company though? Student. Because I’m always learning.

This business was paid for their time by Square.

The best thing is that it’s built into it, so people can insert their chips directly on the POS rather than an additional piece.

I like that. It’s more streamlined. It’s smaller.

I like that it’s backwards compatible, ‘cause I can still use my same old iPad. I don’t have to get a new iPad for it.

Square Stand

and that updates to our website, so that way everything’s kind of integrated. We don’t have to go to the website

and the POS and update both. It’s just one or the other, which is super helpful.

POS options

POS options

And the film scanner was a really expensive piece of equipment, so just getting those two pieces of equipment really made us a legitimate

It allows you to dictate how much money you want to pay back at a time.

And that really helps with paying back your loans because you’re not using your outside money, you’re using money you just acquired.

We’ve been able to do it three or four times, and it’s really helped us grow our business vertically.

Loans

So our loyalty program’s a cool way of getting customers to come back.

It also helps us to have visibility on what our day looks like.

When you’re working as an artist, or a tattooer, or a piercer, they live and die by their appointment book.

It’s a great indicator of what their day is going to be like

when they look at how many available slots they have and how some walk-ins are going to fill in those slots.

It even gives them the ability to know what their potential earning is going to be that month.

Square Appointments

Square Appointments

Messages
